  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- International cooperation between agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting large/suspicious transactions\n- Maintaining comprehensive financial records\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset confiscation\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional license revocation\n\n7. Emerging Areas\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced technological surveillance\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
